    <thetext>Description of problem:
In lastpipe mode nested pipelines can cause a segmentation fault.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
bash-4.3.42-5.fc25

How reproducible:
Always

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Create a script with below commands :
  #!/usr/bin/bash
  set -E
  shopt -s lastpipe
  trap -- &apos;true&apos; ERR
  true | { true | false; }

2. Execute the script

Actual results:
bash crashes with segmentation fault

Expected results:
bash should not crash

Additional info:
Upstream bug http://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/bug-bash/2014-08/msg00040.html</thetext>
